  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Pregnancy First Contact - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pregnancy_first_contact">Pregnancy First Contact</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_contact">CARE CONTACT</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pregnancy_first_contact">Pregnancy First Contact</xref>
 is when a pregnant woman first contacted the NHS to access 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_antenatal">Antenatal</xref>
 / pregnancy care.        </p>
    <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pregnancy_first_contact">Pregnancy First Contact</xref>
 may be with a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONAL</xref>, and includes self referrals to 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_maternity_service">Maternity Services</xref>
 during the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_maternity_episode">Maternity Episode</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
